cast.overview: Suspicious that her colleague is responsible for a series of mysterious patient deaths, a nurse risks her own life to uncover the truth.
cast.title: The Good Nurse

details.biography: Christine Healy (born June 13, 1950, in Buffalo, New York) is an American television and film actress known for her recurring roles on shows such as ER, The Days and Nights of Molly Dodd, and The Practice. She has appeared in numerous television series including St. Elsewhere, L.A. Law, Star Trek: Deep Space Nine, Criminal Minds, and Dr. Quinn, Medicine Woman. Her film credits include Like Father Like Son (1987), Voices Within: The Lives of Truddi Chase (1990), and Murder by Numbers (2002). Healy is recognized for her ability to portray complex characters, often appearing in dramas and professional roles. She has been married to actor and writer Paul Linke since 1991, and they have one child.
details.name: Christine Healy
